A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Election Law – Local Boards of Elections – Language–Related Assistance
3 FOR the purpose of requiring the State Board of Elections to determine whether there is a
4 significant and substantial need for language–related assistance in certain
5 languages by a local board of elections during an election based on certain criteria;
6 requiring local boards to provide certain language–related assistance and materials
7 in voting and elections to certain voters in certain languages; requiring local boards
8 to make reasonable efforts to recruit election judges who are fluent in certain
9 languages; and generally relating to language–related assistance.
10 BY adding to
11 Article – Election Law
12 Section 15.5–101 through 15.5–106 to be under the new title “Title 15.5.
13 Language–Related Assistance”
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2022 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Election Law
19 TITLE 15.5. LANGUAGE–RELATED ASSISTANCE.
20 15.5–101.
21 IN THIS TITLE, “LIMITED ENGLISH PROFICIENCY” MEANS THAT AN
22 INDIVIDUAL:
23 (1) SPEAKS A PARTICULAR LANGUAGE OTHER THAN ENGLISH;
