19 FOR EACH DESIGNATED LANGUAGE UNDER § 15.5–102 OF THIS TITLE, THE
20 LANGUAGE–RELATED ASSISTANCE AND MATERIALS SHALL INCLUDE:
21 (I) TRANSLATED REGISTRATION AND VOTING FORMS AND
22 NOTICES;
23 (II) ELECTION–RELATED MATERIALS;
24 (III) SIGNAGE AT ALL EARLY VOTING CENTERS AND POLLING
25 PLACES IN DESIGNATED LANGUAGES NOTIFYING VOTERS THAT LANGUAGE
26 ASSISTANCE AND TELEPHONE INTERPRETERS ARE AVAILABLE; AND
27 (IV) SAMPLE BALLOTS AND OTHER MATERIALS OR
28 INFORMATION RELATING TO THE ELECTORAL PROCESS.
29 (2) IN THE CASE OF A LANGUAGE THAT IS ORAL OR UNWRITTEN,
30 INCLUDING SIGN LANGUAGE, THE LOCAL BOARD MAY PROVIDE ONLY ORAL
31 INSTRUCTIONS, ASSISTANCE, OR OTHER INFORMATION RELATING TO THE
32 ELECTORAL PROCESS IN THE APPLICABLE LANGUAGE.

